reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars YES YOU NEED THIS!!!!
reviews.reviewText: I haven’t even used it yet and I love it! I installed it in my car attached both sets of bottom straps to my console and I can get into my console without it sliding back or restricting access to anything! It’s a tad wide for the space between my seats. BUT it works great because there aren’t crannies for things to get lost in. I love that it’s a more solid material with many storage spaces for smaller things as opposed to my previous “storage net” which stretched WAY too much and prevented access to the rear passenger climate controls and USB ports when I put my purse there - it would just act like a stretchy hammock for my purse and the holes were huge and things would fall through them. I love the amount of storage it has and that it doesn’t interfere with my personal space or the rear controls but also stays in place.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Lots of storage
reviews.reviewText: This product is too large for my car but my car is very small and doesn’t have a lot of storage. I decided to keep it anyways because of that very reason & it does have lots of pockets. The bottom is fairly sturdy however the sides are mesh so of course they’ll bend and fold over. I use this to store my sunglasses, snacks and water bottles, wet wipes & occasionally my wallet. I haven’t filled it up completely at one given time, so I’m not sure how much weight it’ll hold. However it was easy to install and gets used every time I drive my car.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My sister was so happy to get this for her Christmas gift, she won't have to keep reaching for her purse any longer, always put on her console between her seats and always fell in back seat. She is delighted with it. Nicely made, extra pockets also built in so you can put in some paper and ink pen, bottle water if you want, maybe a small umbrella that folds up. At your fingertips, no more reaching in your floor board for your purse. Awesome!

reviews.reviewText: It looks great in the photos and I love the idea. I've been frustrated with "stuff" sliding off into the back seat. Unfortunately, I can't seem to find places to anchor this the way it needs to be to solve my dilemma.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Fits perfectly in my car. Perfect pockets for things I keep in my car (sunblock, lotion, hand sanitizer, etc.). The large pocket fits my purse perfectly. The only issue is that is smells like awful perfume. I checked to see if I accidentally ordered a scented version. I did not. I had to take it out of my car because the smell was giving me a headache and my kids were complaining about the smell in the car. I am leaving it outside for a few days to see if the smell goes away. If the perfume wasn’t so strong this would be a perfect product. If heavy perfume doesn’t bother you, then this product will be fine for you. Update… I left it outside for about a week and the smell is still really strong.
